      <title>Singleton</title>
      <link href="/2023/05/27/c/"/>
      <url>/2023/05/27/c/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="\assets\css\APlayer.min.css"><script src="\assets\js\APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><script class="meting-secondary-script-marker" src="\assets\js\Meting.min.js"></script><h1 id="1-What-is-Singleton"><a href="#1-What-is-Singleton" class="headerlink" title="1. What is Singleton"></a>1. What is Singleton</h1><p>A singleton class is a special type of class in object-oriented programming which can have only one object or instance at a time. </p><h1 id="2-Steps-to-implement-Singleton-class-in-C"><a href="#2-Steps-to-implement-Singleton-class-in-C" class="headerlink" title="2. Steps to implement Singleton class in C++"></a>2. Steps to implement Singleton class in C++</h1><ol><li>Make all the constructor of the class private;</li><li>Delete the copy constructor  of the class;</li><li>Make a private static pointer that can point the the same class object;</li><li>Make a public static method that returns the pointer to the same class object.</li></ol><h1 id="3-Two-different-cases"><a href="#3-Two-different-cases" class="headerlink" title="3. Two different cases"></a>3. Two different cases</h1><h2 id="3-1-An-instance-of-Singleton-Class-is-created-beforehand"><a href="#3-1-An-instance-of-Singleton-Class-is-created-beforehand" class="headerlink" title="3.1 An instance of Singleton Class is created beforehand"></a>3.1 An instance of Singleton Class is created beforehand</h2><pre class="line-numbers language-c++" data-language="c++"><code class="language-c++">class Singleton &#123;public:Singleton(const Singleton&amp;) &#x3D; delete;static Singleton* getInstance();private:Singleton(const std::string&amp;);static Singleton* singleton_;std::string&amp; value_;&#125;std::string value;&#x2F;&#x2F; ** difference **&#x2F;&#x2F; initialize an instance beforehandSingleton* Singleton::singleton_ &#x3D; new Singleton(value);Singleton* Singleton::getInstance() &#123;return singleton_;&#125;Singleton::Singleton(const std::string&amp; value): value_(value) &#123;&#125;<span aria-hidden="true" class="line-numbers-rows"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></code></pre><h2 id="3-2-When-the-instance-is-created-without-using-the-getInstance-method-to-create-the-Singleton-Class"><a href="#3-2-When-the-instance-is-created-without-using-the-getInstance-method-to-create-the-Singleton-Class" class="headerlink" title="3.2 When the instance is created without using the getInstance() method to create the Singleton Class"></a>3.2 When the instance is created without using the getInstance() method to create the Singleton Class</h2><pre class="line-numbers language-c++" data-language="c++"><code class="language-c++">class Singleton &#123;public:Singleton(const Singleton&amp;) &#x3D; delete;static Singleton* getInstance(const std::string&amp;);private:Singleton(const std::string&amp;);static Singleton* singleton_;std::string value_;&#125;Singleton* Singleton::singleton_ &#x3D; nullptr;Singleton* Singleton::getInstance(const std::string&amp; value) &#123;&#x2F;&#x2F; ** difference **&#x2F;&#x2F; only initialize an instance when usedif (singleton_ &#x3D;&#x3D; nullptr) &#123;singleton_ &#x3D; new Singleton(value);&#125;return singleton_;&#125;Singleton::Singleton(const std::string&amp; value): value_(value) &#123;&#125;<span aria-hidden="true" class="line-numbers-rows"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></code></pre>]]></content>
      
      
      
